(44, 2, 25, 44, 2, 29, 30, 'I foresaw the Lord always before my face', 'Connection of David and Christ', 'Both passages emphasize David''s prophetic role regarding Christ. Acts 2:25 mentions David''s foresight, while Acts 2:29-30 highlights his prophecy about Christ''s resurrection and kingship.', 'prophecy', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 25, 43, 16, 32, 32, 'he is on my right hand', 'Presence of God in Trials', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine presence during moments of abandonment. In Acts, David speaks of the Lord''s constant presence, while in John, Jesus acknowledges the Fatherâ€™s presence despite his disciples scattering.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
