(44, 2, 26, 19, 71, 23, 23, 'my heart rejoice', 'Joy and Redemption Connection', 'Both passages emphasize rejoicing and the hope found in redemption. Acts 2:26 speaks of the heart rejoicing, while Psalms 71:23 highlights rejoicing in song due to redemption.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 26, 19, 30, 11, 11, 'my heart rejoice, and my tongue was glad', 'Joy and Gladness in Suffering', 'Both passages emphasize a transformation from sorrow to joy. Acts 2:26 speaks of the heart rejoicing and the tongue being glad, while Psalms 30:11 describes mourning turned into dancing and being girded with gladness.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 26, 19, 22, 22, 24, 'my flesh shall rest in hope', 'Connection of Hope and Praise', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of hope and praise amidst affliction. Acts 2:26 speaks of resting in hope, while Psalms 22:24 assures that God hears the cries of the afflicted, encouraging praise.', 'theme', 0.3, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 27, 19, 16, 10, 10, 'thou wilt not leave my soul in hell', 'Connection of Resurrection Assurance', 'Both passages emphasize that God will not leave the soul in hell and will not allow His Holy One to see corruption. This connection highlights the theme of divine protection and resurrection.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 27, 44, 2, 31, 31, 'neither wilt thou suffer thine Holy One to see corruption', 'Resurrection of Christ', 'Both passages emphasize that Christ''s soul was not left in hell and his flesh did not see corruption, highlighting the significance of the resurrection. This connection underscores the fulfillment of prophecy regarding Jesus'' resurrection.', 'prophecy', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 27, 66, 1, 18, 18, 'suffer thine Holy One to see corruption', 'Connection of Life and Death', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of life after death. Acts 2:27 speaks of not leaving the soul in hell, while Revelation 1:18 declares the speaker''s eternal life and authority over hell and death.', 'theme', 0.363, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 27, 66, 20, 13, 13, 'soul in hell', 'Connection of Death and Judgment', 'This connection highlights the theme of death and the afterlife. Acts 2:27 speaks of not leaving the soul in hell, while Revelation 20:13 discusses hell delivering up the dead for judgment.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
