(44, 2, 29, 16, 3, 16, 16, NULL, 'Connection of David''s Sepulchre', 'This connection highlights the mention of David''s sepulchre in both passages. Acts 2:29 refers to David''s burial, while Nehemiah 3:16 specifically mentions the sepulchres of David, linking the two texts thematically.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 29, 44, 7, 8, 9, 'patriarch David', 'Connection of Patriarchs and David', 'Both passages emphasize the role of patriarchs in Israel''s history. Acts 2:29 references David as a patriarch, while Acts 7:8-9 discusses the twelve patriarchs, linking their significance in God''s covenant.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 29, 58, 7, 4, 4, 'patriarch David', 'Connection Between David and Abraham', 'This connection highlights the significance of patriarchs in biblical lineage. Both David and Abraham are referenced as key figures, emphasizing their roles in the faith community.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 30, 19, 132, 11, 18, NULL, 'David''s Throne and Christ', 'This connection highlights the promise made to David regarding his lineage. Both passages emphasize that God will raise up a descendant from David to sit on the throne, linking the covenant with David to the establishment of Christ''s reign.', 'prophecy', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
