(44, 2, 30, 42, 1, 31, 33, NULL, 'Connection of David''s Throne', 'This connection highlights the promise of a descendant from David''s lineage who will reign. Both passages emphasize the theme of Jesus being given the throne of David, linking his kingship to God''s covenant with David.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 31, 44, 2, 27, 27, NULL, 'Resurrection Prophecy Connection', 'Both passages emphasize that the soul will not be left in hell and that the flesh will not see corruption. This connection highlights the prophetic nature of the statements regarding the resurrection of Christ.', 'prophecy', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 31, 19, 16, 10, 10, NULL, 'Resurrection and Corruption Connection', 'Both passages emphasize that the soul will not be left in hell and that the Holy One will not see corruption. This connection highlights the prophetic nature of Psalm 16:10 as it is referenced in Acts 2:31 regarding the resurrection of Christ.', 'prophecy', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 31, 44, 13, 35, 35, 'his flesh did see corruption', 'Resurrection and Corruption', 'Both passages emphasize that the Holy One''s flesh did not see corruption, highlighting the significance of Christ''s resurrection. The connection underscores the fulfillment of prophecy regarding the preservation of Christ''s body after death.', 'prophecy', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 31, 60, 1, 11, 12, 'the resurrection of Christ', 'Connection of Prophecy and Suffering', 'This connection highlights the prophetic nature of the sufferings and resurrection of Christ. Both passages emphasize the foretelling of Christ''s sufferings and the subsequent glory, linking the resurrection to the message preached by the apostles.', 'prophecy', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 32, 44, 3, 15, 15, NULL, 'Resurrection Witnesses Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the resurrection of Jesus and the witnesses to this event. The phrase ''whom God hath raised'' links the two verses, highlighting the continuity of the message about Jesus'' resurrection.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 32, 44, 1, 8, 8, 'witnesses', 'Witnesses of Jesus'' Resurrection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of witnesses. Acts 2:32 states that the apostles are witnesses of Jesus'' resurrection, while Acts 1:8 highlights their mission to be witnesses in various regions.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 32, 42, 24, 46, 48, 'we all are witnesses', 'Witnesses of Christ''s Resurrection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of witnesses to Jesus'' resurrection. Acts 2:32 states, ''we all are witnesses,'' while Luke 24:48 declares, ''ye are witnesses of these things.'' This connection highlights the continuity of the witness theme in the early church.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 32, 43, 15, 27, 27, 'witnesses', 'Witnessing to Jesus'' Resurrection', 'This connection highlights the theme of bearing witness. Acts 2:32 speaks of the apostles as witnesses to Jesus'' resurrection, while John 15:27 emphasizes their role as witnesses due to their close relationship with Him.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 32, 43, 20, 26, 31, 'this Jesus hath God raised up', 'Resurrection and Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the resurrection of Jesus and the importance of belief. Acts 2:32 states that Jesus was raised, while John 20:29 highlights the blessing of those who believe without seeing.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
