(44, 2, 33, 44, 5, 31, 31, 'by the right hand of God exalted', 'Exaltation and Role of Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the exaltation of Christ at God''s right hand. They highlight His role as a source of repentance and forgiveness for Israel.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 33, 43, 14, 26, 26, 'the promise of the Holy Ghost', 'Connection of the Holy Ghost', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Holy Ghost. Acts 2:33 mentions the Holy Ghost being shed forth, while John 14:26 describes the Holy Ghost as the Comforter sent by the Father.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 33, 43, 16, 7, 15, 'the promise of the Holy Ghost', 'Connection of the Holy Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Holy Spirit as a Comforter and guide. Acts 2:33 refers to the outpouring of the Holy Spirit, which aligns with John 16:7-15''s promise of the Spirit coming after Jesus'' departure.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 33, 40, 28, 18, 18, 'by the right hand of God', 'Authority and Power of Jesus', 'This connection highlights the exaltation of Jesus and His authority. Acts 2:33 mentions Jesus being ''by the right hand of God,'' which aligns with Matthew 28:18''s declaration of ''All power is given unto me.''', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 33, 41, 16, 19, 19, 'by the right hand of God exalted', 'Exaltation and Position of Christ', 'Both passages emphasize Christ''s exaltation and position at the right hand of God. Acts 2:33 refers to Him being ''by the right hand of God exalted,'' while Mark 16:19 states He ''sat on the right hand of God.''', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 33, 48, 3, 14, 14, NULL, 'Connection of the Holy Spirit Promise', 'Both passages emphasize the promise of the Spirit. Acts 2:33 mentions the Holy Ghost being shed forth, while Galatians 3:14 speaks of receiving the promise of the Spirit through faith.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
