(44, 2, 34, 58, 1, 13, 13, 'Sit thou on my right hand', 'Connection of Divine Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the phrase ''Sit thou on my right hand,'' indicating a position of authority. This connection highlights the significance of being at God''s right hand, underscoring the exaltation of the one addressed.', 'quotation', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
